title: Daenerys Loses Jon
body:
A lot of people have been looking at the following image as happening at Winterfell:

While I don’t disagree, what some people are not noticing is her costume. She has red on top and no ascot.

Look at her winter outfit we see elsewhere:

Where is the obvious red in her top? Where is her ascot?

It’s not there because it’s not the same outfit. Rather, it looks like this one:

It’s a much darker outfit with a clearer red top banding.

Costume changes usually represent a shift of some sort. This outfit is very dark and intimidating, and yet Daenerys looks devastated in that image at the top. Why?

I don’t think it is after the Battle of Winterfell. I think it is after she has lost the support of Jon or even just readying herself to fight against a former ally.

summary: “Oh, my sweet summer child," Old Nan said quietly, "what do you know of fear? Fear is for the winter, my little lord, when the...
body:
“Oh, my sweet summer child,“ Old Nan said quietly, "what do you know of fear?
Fear is for the winter, my little lord, when the snows fall a hundred feet
deep and the ice wind comes howling out of the north. Fear is for the long
night, when the sun hides its face for years at a time, and little children
are born and live and die all in darkness while the direwolves grow gaunt and
hungry, and the white walkers move through the woods”

body:
In Defence of Catelyn Stark

I have had enough of people saying Catelyn abused Jon Snow. Saying that Jon Snow was abused as a child is severely downplaying actual abuse and it’s consequences. Jon is not Harry Potter and the starts were never the Dursleys to him.

Catelyn Stark loved her Lord husband with everything she had. Her Lord husband was known as the most honorable man in Westeros. When the most honorable man in Westeros who was her husband and supposedly in love with her, returned with a bastard child in his hand, of course she was pissed. She is human for god’ sake. You don’t want your boyfriend to text his ex, her husband had a baby with another woman. And she didn’t hate Jon Snow. She never did. She just couldn’t love him.

Jon was fed and educated with all the legitimate Stark children. He was loved in Winterfell, just not by Catelyn.

Also, Jon himself never seems to hold any of it against Catelyn. Jon understood.
